Conclusion
--------------------------------------------------------
The original four lines work because they are a perfect closed loop: the formal skid (haiku → meme) enacts the thematic skid (Mario → abyss). The poem is not just about Mario; it is about any system where the very properties that let us go fast also guarantee we will occasionally go too far. And when we do, the public chorus will reduce our catastrophe to a two-syllable moral judgement, delivered at the speed of a 60 Hz refresh rate. [end of text]


